review_blob:
Yes, my kind of beer.

American style hop-first ale. Loads of piney and citrusy aroma. Bitter as it is supposed to be, but not overwhelming - balanced well with the limited strength. Just a perfect beer for when visiting a bar wanting that American style ale, but avoiding the BWs and IIPAs in order retain functional capacity

Loads of esters in the aroma - bananas, cloves and perhaps apricot.

Not really that Bock-like. A bit on the dry side and rather light in colour, so its more like a weizen, just a little bit stronger.
Really not my favorite among DIPAs. Too malty and biscuity. Its more like a BW, if you ask me! But by no means a bad brew..

Great looking red beer!
Decent brew.Slightly sweet and bready aroma.
Taste is dry and a little bland. It should be either more malty sweet or a little more hoppy. Body is thin. But, as with all products from carlsberg, its always reliable, and compared to a lot of BORING danish microbrew, this one is the better choice. This beer was retired som years ago, and is now a seasonal. I remember it as having more malt in the old version.Then again  perhaps Ive just changed.

Nice!

Wondeful aroma with loads of dark berries and a slightly hoppy nose. 

Thick texture, roasted but in contrast to many other beers this dark, it has no astringency or harshness in the finish. Very complex and full of flavour, but easy to drink at the same time,

This is damn tasty.

Clean, malty beer. Dry, crisp and hoppy finish. Though it is described as English, I still find that the hop-profile has an American touch. Very refreshing!
UPDATED: MAY 14, 2008

Almost as bad as Tuborg Lite.

Looks good though - clear yellow with lasting white foam.

Terrible smell of canned corn, sweet and bland flavor.

Foul

Ruby coloured, small off white head.

Aroma of citrusy/resiny hops, cara-malts and a little fusel - not bothersome, though.

Flavor is sweet and bitter. Not as bitter as I expected.  Slightly acidic finish. Thick and full body. Suprisingly not very sticky, considering the ABV.

Realy very nice, but ive had several barley wines very similar to this. Then again, it is one of my preferred styles, so ill give it good marks.

Rated entirely according to the Radler-style. This should not be rated alongside fx. imp. stouts.

Great refreshing drink with a nice lemon aroma. Lemon complements the bitterness of pilsener extremely well.
UPDATED: MAY 1, 2008

Truly a dissapointment!

Pours thick and black.Very nice liquorice aroma. Rather bitter, but  a really thin body Slightly unpleasant pungent aftertaste.

There are much better porters out there. This beer is a manifestation of a common problem with a  lot of danish microbrew: mediocrity.

I like this!

All beers of this styule are quite sweet. But compared to other danish "hvidtl", this is less sweet, more malty and has a distinct touch of saaz-bitterness.

Especially nice around christmas.

Aah, the beer of choice for many danish drunks roaming the streets! Had many Elephants in my life - just to sympathize.


Pretty much just a fortified pale lager - warm, alcoholic, malty. I like it. 

I know this isnt comme il faut, but if you want to get in the mood walking to a metal-concert, a couple of cans of this stuff gets the friggin job done

Very malty,rather dry with a touch of smoke in the aftertaste. 

Nice and complex. Bought 54 of them really cheap in Aying. Im used to liking hoppy beers, so the first botlle was so-so. But this one really grows on you, so Im glad i have a stash..
But I will probably have to rerate after 20 or 30 of them. ;-)

Pretty decent beer.

Beautiful colour, nice malty/caramel aroma.

But if they want to use american hops, make sure that its more detectable.

The beer is not bad. Its just not good enough and too anomymous to justify its price-tag
UPDATED: MAY 2, 2008

Not every beer has to be a life changing experience.

This beer is obviously not amazing. However it is an adjunct-free natural product and the strict quality control of Carlsberg ensures uniform quality - if stored correctly, of course, which seems to be problem in many supermarkets.

In my opinion, it would be nice with a little more flavour. Especially some more bitterness.

Not bad, not exciting.

Good hoppy aroma, rather bittter, naturally.

I would like some more malt. Too thin for my liking. Slightly astringent finish.
beer_name: Rise r Marstal India Pale Ale

review_blob: hmmmm.....it's not that it doesn't taste OK. It's just not very interesting. The aroma is nice. However, if you're going for a beer of this kind you'd expect more flavour. Maybe it's a good introduction, if you are not familiar with stouts.

Awesome! The aroma reminded me of really good fresh made coffee. Not bad. Taste and palate is silk smooth and very well balanced. You will find a stout that is stronger and heavier, but few that are more delicious.

This bottle had a red label and an abv of 5.5%.

Nice colour. The aroma is fruit and hops. The flavour is a bit on the sweet-malt side. A little more hops would be nice. In my mind very drinkable nevertheless.

It's a good looking beer. Not doubt about that. The flavour is spicy and unusual. Pretty malty. Not bad. But the aroma reminds me a little of once when I opened a regular pilsner that had been left in the sun...and in my opinion that is not good......
UPDATED: MAY 25, 2008
Looks great black with the milkshake head. Still, I prefer beer with regular carbonation. It's a good stout nevertheless.
I have overlooked this one for too long. One of Carlsberg's very best beers. Strong and full in taste. The bitter aftertaste complements the sweetness of alcohol pretty well.
What is this?? Bottled, slightly yellow mineral water with a content of alcohol. I don't think it tastes bad, but then again I like mineral water too. In terms of a beer it is really bad, though.
Well, another beer without flavour!! Has nothing. It doesn'r scare anyone off, but then again, it's really boring.
Almost perfect aroma of liqorice and chocolate. Nice appereance too. The flavour is a little too dry and bitter for my taste.
UPDATED: APR 16, 2008

Pink. Very carbonated. Spiced with elder berries, i think they are called. Why do they launch a beer like this during winter?
Decent refreshing summer beer and an OK attempt to make something out of the  ordinary. That deserves some credit.
Smells extremely hoppy, which is nice. The flavor doesn"t quite match the aroma, too bad. A but too thin.
hmmmmmm.... I heard many people praise this one. It looks good and has a nice aroma. To me, it,s sweetness was somewhat nauseating, though. Strange, cause i generally like sweet beers.

The best Christmas brew from Carlsberg/Tuborg. I really like it. Nice full-bodied. Almost no head, though, which is a draw-back.(I dont understand the other ratings that say, it has a nice head. Initially, it has a head, but it disappears very quickly) The colour is nice
Full bodied. Port-like. One of the best.
Avoid this beer! Has nothing going for it. Its an attempt to get to teenagers, who really dont like beer.
